knowledge_graph.description: Neutron Holdings, Inc., doing business under the name Lime, formerly LimeBike, is an American transportation company based in San Francisco, California. It runs electric scooters, electric bikes and electric mopeds in more than 200 cities in nearly 30 countries around the world.

related_questions.question: What is lime used for?
related_questions.snippet: Lime's Myriad Uses Various forms of lime are used in environmental, metallurgical, construction, and chemical/industrial applications, and more. The fastest growing use of lime is in environmental applications, where lime is used to comply with air, drinking water, wastewater, and solid waste regulations.
related_questions.title: Uses of Lime - The National Lime Association

related_questions.question: What is is lime?
related_questions.snippet: Lime is an inorganic material composed primarily of calcium oxides and hydroxides. It is also the name for calcium oxide which occurs as a product of coal-seam fires and in altered limestone xenoliths in volcanic ejecta.
related_questions.title: Lime (material) - Wikipedia

related_questions.question: What does lime do for your body?
related_questions.snippet: Limes contain antioxidants, which have been shown to help reduce inflammation and even help prevent certain chronic illnesses. The high levels of Vitamin C found in limes can help protect you from infection and speed up your body's healing process. Citrus fruits have been shown to help keep kidney stones at bay.
related_questions.title: Health Benefits of Limes - WebMD

related_questions.question: What is lime water good for?
related_questions.snippet: Drinking adequate amounts of water with lime may provide some benefits, such as aiding weight management, skin health, and helping prevent kidney stones. The body needs water to survive, and drinking enough is crucial for maintaining optimal health. Water ensures the human body is adequately hydrated.
